No. No, no, nothing like that. And - when he - when he'd been in office or quite a long time - and - he really knew the ins and outs of the Lodge business the - th
ey used to look to him for - guidance, on certain subjects. You could always depend on him giving an answer you see. To certain questions.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7670325 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10891958\charrsid15805719 How did you get on with your brothers and sisters?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13597539 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10891958\charrsid15805719 Oh generally speaking very good - very well.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7670325 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10891958\charrsid15805719 Was there any one of them that you felt particularly close to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13597539 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10891958\charrsid15805719 
No, I - I was always friendly with my elder brother 'cos he were the next - there were nobody between us, you see. And I was always - I was very fond of my eldest sister.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7670325 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10891958\charrsid15805719 Who did you play with, brothers and sisters or neighbours?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13597539 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10891958\charrsid15805719 
Well - brothers and sisters generally about our own age but there was always - in those days you see there were bigger families and there was always plenty of children to play with and it didn't matter what 
sex. You could always play at - at - different things. You see, there wasn't the traffic in those days because - see as next week when - or - or this week rather when Shrove Tuesday comes along - we could always go out into the road and play marbles and s
huttlecock and - we always had a bowler. A }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7163663\charrsid15805719 hoop}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10891958\charrsid15805719 
 - an iron hoop we used to say, in order we could run up and down the streets with - with no hindrance from traffic.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7670325 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10891958\charrsid15805719 Generally then you would play out in the street would you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13597539 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10891958\charrsid15805719 Play out in the street
. Generally - or in the fields, because on Walker Street - there's only houses on one side. There was always fields other side of the road, fly kites and - play cricket and football and so on. Oh yes. And on one occasion - my father made us a special - wh
a
t you used to call a wallet - for the - for the cotton or the string. Mechanical sort - hand - hand propelled you see. And - on one occasion I got my kite - very high up. And - all at once the string snapped and I thought, that's the end of that so I just
 went home and packed it in. But after coming home from school, I'd been to school in the afternoon, after coming home from school and walking round in the area I found that the kite was still flying. The cotton had caught on the chimney pot as it travel}
{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid729553\charrsid15805719 l}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10891958\charrsid15805719 ed
 and - and the gentleman in the house went up and got this thing down for me, yes. Yes. It had been flying there all afternoon without any help. I remember that very well. But - you see, those fields were privately owned and at the end of Walker Street wa
s
 a clay pit where they used - got the clay out for the pottery. To the pottery croft there where they made stone bottles - for Steven Drink, and things like that you see. Oh yes, the - they had - a lot of girls working there one time. I remember there was
 always a pond in the middle of these fields as well and so we - when we played cricket or few our kites in there we always used to look out for the local bobby, you see. And we made a beeline for the nearest - place of hiding of course.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7670325 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10891958\charrsid15805719 Were you allowed to get dirty playing out as a child, did your parents used to moan at you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13597539 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10891958\charrsid15805719 
Well we - you can't play very well without getting dirty and sometimes - we'd - tear our trousers, well of course - that wasn't very well received at home you see. Meant more work for mother. You see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7670325 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10891958\charrsid15805719 Could you play with anyone you pleased or were there certain children you were told not to play with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13597539 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10891958\charrsid15805719 No, no I don't think so, generally speaking in that area there was - fairly decent and there was no - no trouble in that respect.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7670325 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10891958\charrsid15805719 You had a lot of activities associated with the church didn't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13597539 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10891958\charrsid15805719 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7670325 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10891958\charrsid15805719 There were no other youth organizations then in the area?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13597539 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10891958\charrsid15805719 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7670325 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10891958\charrsid15805719 In your free time did you have any hobbies, you told me you kept rabbits?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13597539 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10891958\charrsid15805719 We kept rabbits, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7670325 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10891958\charrsid15805719 Did you collect anything, cards or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13597539 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10891958\charrsid15805719 Oh yes. Cigarette cards. Oh yes, cigarette cards.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7670325 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10891958\charrsid15805719 And you did a lot of gardening?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13597539 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10891958\charrsid15805719 We had a lot of gardening.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7670325 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10891958\charrsid15805719 You used to help your father and your grandfather?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13597539 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10891958\charrsid15805719 Yes. And - we had - horse chestnuts you see, and we used to play cobblers, you know, you get the horse chestnuts on a string and -

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7670325 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10891958\charrsid15805719 What they call conkers now?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13597539 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10891958\charrsid15805719 Call conkers, we used to call it cobblers in those days. Well - I got 
