\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7670325 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10891958\charrsid15805719 They just rotted?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13597539 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10891958\charrsid15805719 No, until I saw a ring of something coming up one day. And - they all took root you see and - yes, there's quite a lot of }{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7163663\charrsid15805719 horse chestnut}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10891958\charrsid15805719  trees are in the area that was grown from those. 'Course the real thing to do was to put them in the chimney to harden th
em you see. That was the old fashioned way of doing it. You see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7670325 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10891958\charrsid15805719 Did you ever go fishing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13597539 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10891958\charrsid15805719 
Oh yes, go to the local stream to fish for tiddlers and redbreasts and - but not in any stream - we were always warned against deep water.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7670325 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10891958\charrsid15805719 Did you cycle?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13597539 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10891958\charrsid15805719 Oh - yes, I cycled, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7670325 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10891958\charrsid15805719 Did you go for walks?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13597539 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10891958\charrsid15805719 Oh yes, we used to often go walks you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7670325 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10891958\charrsid15805719 Would you go with anyone particular?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13597539 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10891958\charrsid15805719 No, just - just friends, just schoolmates.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7670325 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10891958\charrsid15805719 Did you take part in any sports?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13597539 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10891958\charrsid15805719 Not - no
t organised. No. We - you see, those days we - the children had to - they had to make their own fun and - form their own games. And there was all kinds of games such as - rusty bum, finger and thumb. You see, that's one of the old expressions. Used to get
 
a line of boys you see, with their heads between their legs and - take it in turns, the furthest you could jump over the - furthest boys back you see. And then call out - call out this and if you gave the wrong answer of course you had another jump. And t
hings like that you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7670325 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10891958\charrsid15805719 Did you ever go to a theatre or a concert hall in those days, as a lad while you were still at school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13597539 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10891958\charrsid15805719 Well there - there weren't anything like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7670325 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10891958\charrsid15805719 Or cinemas?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13597539 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10891958\charrsid15805719 No, no cinemas. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7163663\charrsid15805719 The only cinemas were the first 
cinemas that came into our area came with the local fair. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10891958\charrsid15805719 They had Hilltop Wastes and Eastwood }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12523590\charrsid15805719 Statis}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10891958\charrsid15805719 . }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7163663\charrsid15805719 I suppose it should have been Eastwood Statis, but they always called it Eastwood Statis. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid10891958\charrsid15805719 It was Hilltop Weeks was held on that spare ground in front of the Three }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12994918\charrsid15805719 T}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10891958\charrsid15805719 
ons or in a field nearby. Of course there's housed built on it now. And - when those houses were built it was transferred to the - to the field where Walker Street school is built now. You see, well - there was always a cinematograph show came t
here. As part of the fair. And there was these - large mechanical organs you know. And dancing girls. And - the man in the - the frock coat and silk hat with a long cane and he would point first to the people then to the entrance and - used to pay tuppenc
e.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7670325 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10891958\charrsid15805719 You used to go as a child when it was on there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13597539 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10891958\charrsid15805719 
When it was on there. Yes. And - when you get to my part time job I'll tell you something else about that perhaps. You see, there were no cinemas, that was the only - the introduction to any cinema in the area at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7670325 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10891958\charrsid15805719 Did your parents give you any pocket money?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13597539 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10891958\charrsid15805719 
Well - yes, only a few coppers though. Same as I say, when were at the Breach we had a ha'penny a week, well gradually it'd rise you see, according to - to when we started to work you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7670325 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10891958\charrsid15805719 You started off with a ha'penny?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13597539 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10891958\charrsid15805719 Yes. Yes. A ha'penny a week, yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7670325 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10891958\charrsid15805719 What would you spend it on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13597539 AS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10891958\charrsid15805719 Well sweets generally. Then - unless it was - bonfire night and of course that went in - fireworks. We could get a string of fa
rthing - a string of lady crackers for a farthing. What would take us half a morning to unravel before we started to let them off, so that was part of the fun. They were all interwoven. Fireworks, little lady crackers about that long.
